                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.0667/4: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the High Commissioner in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-06-25T17:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 25, 1926—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>44. Your telegram No. 55 dated June 22, 3 p.m. Your recommendation to join your
                    colleagues in signing a collective note to the Turkish Government requesting
                    that diplomatic and consular officers be exempted from the payment of
                    consumption and other special taxes recently enacted is approved by the
                    Department.</p>
                <p>The Department presumes that in making a recommendation in this sense you have
                    given due consideration to the difference between your status and that of your
                    colleagues in Turkey and that you think a collective note is the best means of
                    protecting American interests in this case.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
